detailedDescription.articleBody: Assisted reproductive technology includes medical procedures used primarily to address infertility. This subject involves procedures such as in vitro fertilization, intracytoplasmic sperm injection, cryopreservation of gametes or embryos, and/or the use of fertility medication.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: सहायक प्रजनन तकनीक में मुख्य रूप से बांझपन को संबोधित करने के लिए उपयोग की जाने वाली चिकित्सा प्रक्रियाएं शामिल हैं, इस विषय में इन विट्रो निषेचन, इंट्रासाइटोप्लास्मिक शुक्राणु इंजेक्शन, युग्मकों या भ्रूण के क्रायोप्रेज़र्वेशन और / या फ़र्टिलिटी दवा के उपयोग जैसी प्रक्रियाएं शामिल हैं।

detailedDescription.articleBody: A medical laboratory scientist, also traditionally referred to as a clinical laboratory scientist, or medical technologist, is a healthcare professional who performs chemical, hematological, immunologic, histopathological, cytopathological, microscopic, and bacteriological diagnostic analyses on body fluids such as blood, urine, sputum, stool, cerebrospinal fluid, peritoneal fluid, pericardial fluid, and synovial fluid, as well as other specimens.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: एक चिकित्सा प्रयोगशाला वैज्ञानिक, जिसे पारंपरिक रूप से क्लिनिकल प्रयोगशाला वैज्ञानिक या मेडिकल टेक्नोलॉजिस्ट के रूप में भी जाना जाता है, एक स्वास्थ्य देखभाल पेशेवर है, जो रासायनिक, हीमेटोलॉजिकल, इम्युनोलॉजिकल, हिस्टोपैथोलॉजिकल, साइटोपैथोलॉजिकल, माइक्रोस्कोपिक और बैक्टीरियलोलॉजिकल डायग्नोस्टिक विश्लेषणों जैसे रक्त, मूत्र, का प्रदर्शन करता है।

detailedDescription.articleBody: Santa Monica is a beachfront city in western Los Angeles County, California, United States. Situated on Santa Monica Bay, it is bordered on five sides by different neighborhoods of the city of Los Angeles: Pacific Palisades to the north, Brentwood on the northeast, West Los Angeles on the east, Mar Vista on the southeast, and Venice on the south.

detailedDescription.articleBody: A medical illustration is a form of biological illustration that helps to record and disseminate medical, anatomical, and related knowledge.

detailedDescription.articleBody: In medicine, a case report is a detailed report of the symptoms, signs, diagnosis, treatment, and follow-up of an individual patient. Case reports may contain a demographic profile of the patient, but usually describe an unusual or novel occurrence. Some case reports also contain a literature review of other reported cases.
